## Checklist before requesting a review

Github actions will check that these tasks were performed but it will reduce friction if you deal with them beforhand

- [ ] Code style follows black conventions (Checked by [pre-commit](https://github.com/julietterothnemer-design/PAI---Sudoku/blob/main/.github/workflows/CI.yaml#L82) job)
- [ ] Type hints are consistent (Checked by [pyright](https://github.com/julietterothnemer-design/PAI---Sudoku/blob/main/.github/workflows/CI.yaml#L67) job)
- [ ] New lines are covered by tests (Checked by [pytest coverage](https://github.com/julietterothnemer-design/PAI---Sudoku/blob/main/.github/workflows/CI.yaml#L26) job).
- [ ] If documentation is added, it does not raise a warning in sphinx (checked by [sphinx-build](https://github.com/julietterothnemer-design/PAI---Sudoku/blob/main/.github/workflows/CI.yaml#L65) job)
